On 25/07/06, Sandra Dodd <Sandra@...> wrote:

At age 53:

Ludwig van Beethoven completed his Ninth Symphony despite being so
deaf that, at the end of its first performance, he could not hear
whether the audience was applauding.

Best-selling American author Sidney Sheldon began writing his first
novel.

Inventor Walter Hunt patented the safety pin.

Long-time dissident Vaclav Havel became president of Czechoslovakia.

Jimmy Carter facilitated the Camp David accords between Israel and
Egypt.

Robert E. Peary reached the North Pole.

When They Were Your Age


At age 53:

Ludwig van Beethoven completed his Ninth Symphony despite being so
deaf that, at the end of its first performance, he could not hear
whether the audience was applauding.

Best-selling American author Sidney Sheldon began writing his first
novel.

Inventor Walter Hunt patented the safety pin.

Long-time dissident Vaclav Havel became president of Czechoslovakia.

Jimmy Carter facilitated the Camp David accords between Israel and
Egypt.

Robert E. Peary reached the North Pole.

========================================================================
=========

I'm 53 because I was born in 1953.

That must mean everyone is the age of the year they were born.
<g>

Yeah...
Math's not my best area.

Sandra
